Put the flour, sugar, salt into a bowl and mix thoroughly. Then stir in the yeast.Warm the orange juice slightly in a pan.Gently stir the eggs into the flour mixture a little at a time, alternating with the warm orange juice and the butter.Add the raisins and give it a good mix until it forms a smooth dough.Spoon the mixture into two greased bun tins, dariole moulds or 11cm/4Â½in baba tins (savarin moulds).Cover lightly with a tea towel and leave in a warm place for about an hour, or until doubled in size and lightly spongy.Preheat the oven to 180C/350F/Gas 4.Bake in the oven for 10-12 minutes until risen and golden-brown.Remove from the oven and leave to cool on a wire rack.To transport for a picnic, put into a preserve jar with some lemon zest and drizzle, to taste, with elderflower vodka.